*57 Knight of Karana* <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uabazagaroth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Abazagaroth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/24/01 6:39:12 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: non-paly alts</span><hr size=1> &quot;Because some of us weren't given that choice, unless we wanted to die multiple times to lose our levels (and significant time) to get back to 52 after the level cap was imposed.&quot;<br>
<br>
Cry me a river. Explain to me how this is different than the 52 pally that has spent 6 months not leveling? That pally could be 57-60, but they chose to try for their epic. If the epic was as valuable to you as it is to the pally that stays 52 for months on end then maybe you would delevel with multiple deaths to get a shot at it. If your levels are so useful and valuable to you then kill Kunark dragons. If you can't get the group together to kill one then what are you losing by deleveling except some spells/hp and some use of skill points? (and you still keep your skills capped at the level of 54)<br>
<br>
The time that pally that choses to stay 52 is no different than the time someone that was 52+ would lose (potentially, of course someone can get good or bad luck) by deleveling. As to the idea of only putting the books on Kunark dragons, oh, now THERE'S a winner idea (/sarcasm). Talk about being bitter and wanting to take it out on every other paladin out there.<br>
<br>
I have no problem with someone organizing a raid and setting aside epic loot, but the idea of someone rolling for another character is unfair to me. The only way I see it as fair is if:<br>
<br>
1) it is known before the loot is known so that someone doesn't hear the loot and then see there is nothing for their alt they are playing and try to roll on a book that dropped, and<br>
<br>
2) every other paladin on the raid agrees<br>
<br>
I really don't give one rat's ass if your alt cleric helped more than a paladin would, that doesn't give that character the right to roll on epic class specific loot. What if some cleric that doesn't have a paladin as an alt wants to roll? Maybe that cleric thinks that a frost book can be sold for much much more than a tobrin's eyepatch, and so they want to roll on it. They helped just as much as anyone else and more than any paladin, so shouldn't they get to choose what they want to roll on? Of course not. Putting aside all issues of determining who really has an alt of whatever class (considering this is really a pick up raid issue or multiguild raid as on a guild raid none of this would matter) compared to those that are lying or have a friend log on their X class character that is 53+ and claim to be that person on another computer, it is simply not very kosher to roll on epic quest rare drops as another class.<br>
<br>
People that see no problem with this (this particular situation, as I said, guild raids are different) want to have their cake (FD) and eat it too (level past 52). If you want to level or keep your level and want your FD go kill some Kunark Dragons. If you can't get the people together to kill them then you aren't losing too much by deleveling anyway.<br>
<br>
Abazagaroth Katzkortulu<br>
